    "narrative": "For Ghost Ride the WHIP\u2019s May 4th slate, **Mickey Moniak** (72.55) and **Seiya Suzuki** (71.23) headline our offensive output, benefiting from favorable matchups against mediocre pitching. **Mickey Moniak** is in an especially lucrative spot, pairing a 14% boost from park factors with a favorable platoon split; despite a 34% rain risk, his synergy with high-upside secondary assets makes him a must-start. **Josh Naylor** (70.82) also clears the 70-point threshold, thriving against a soft 4.60 xERA from the opposing arm. We are also banking on **Vinnie Pasquantino** (76.21) to anchor the middle of the order, where a favorable wind and a dynamic platoon advantage solidify his status as our highest-projected producer for the day.\n\nThe optimizer leaned heavily into our SB-priority mandate, which pushed **Brice Turang** (60.39) into the starting 2B slot. Conversely, **Trevor Story** (44.70) remains our most difficult bench decision. He performed well enough to be considered, but the brutal matchup against Tarik Skubal\u2019s 2.76 xERA essentially neutralized his utility. While we value **Trevor Story**\u2019s speed profile, the efficiency drop-off against an elite arm was too significant to justify a start, especially with **Kyle Karros** (46.38) and **Jose Caballero** (47.55) offering similar, albeit less risky, floor potential. We are monitoring the weather in the game featuring **Kyle Karros** and **Mickey Moniak** closely; should those games be PPD, we have enough depth to pivot, though the lack of confirmed lineups for **Cole Young** and **Travis Bazzana** keeps our current configuration in a state of tentative readiness.",
